Package org.forgerock.openidm.scheduler

Interface Scheduler

All Known Implementing Classes:
MemoryScheduler, PersistedScheduler
public interface Scheduler
An interface that wraps a Quartz Scheduler.

      String[] getJobNames() throws org.quartz.SchedulerException

    • addJob

      void addJob(org.quartz.JobDetail job, boolean replace) throws org.quartz.SchedulerException
      Adds a job to the scheduler given a JobDetail and whether or not the job should be replaced if it is already scheduled.
      Parameters:
      job - the JobDetail
      replace - true if the job should be replaced; false otherwise
      Throws:
      org.quartz.SchedulerException - if unable to add the job to the scheduler

    • getCurrentlyExecutingJobs

      org.forgerock.json.JsonValue getCurrentlyExecutingJobs() throws org.quartz.SchedulerException, IOException
      Gets the currently executing jobs. Note that this method is not cluster aware and will only return the running jobs for the instance this method was invoked on.
      Returns:
      a JsonValue list of the currently executing jobs
      Throws:
      org.quartz.SchedulerException - if unable to get the list of currently executing jobs
      IOException - if unable to get the list of currently executing jobs
